  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Iran's announcement of reopening the Strait of Hormuz has triggered a massive risk-on rotation with oil plunging 10% below $90, treasury yields falling, and risk assets rallying including Bitcoin breaking $77K. The geopolitical de-escalation removes the immediate stagflation threat from oil >$100, allowing bonds and equities to rally simultaneously in classic intermarket fashion.",
    "regimeImpact": "This shifts the relief rally from oversold technical bounce to fundamentally-driven risk-on rotation, potentially extending duration and broadening beyond mega-cap tech.",
    "actionItems": [
      "BMNR ladder: Bitcoin above $77K and structural $62.3K level suggests rolling up put strikes and potentially taking profits on lower strikes",
      "Short book: Cover energy/oil shorts immediately and consider reducing defensive positioning given regime shift away from stagflation",
      "Duration positioning: Bond rally from falling yields creates opportunity to reduce Maturity overweight and rotate into Growth/High Growth"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil falling to $90 (from >$100 stagflation threshold) removes key macro headwind and supports bond rally.",
      "Bitcoin $77K breakthrough above 10-week highs with geopolitical relief suggests crypto risk-on acceleration.",
      "Treasury yields falling while stocks rally indicates healthy risk-on rotation rather than flight-to-quality.",
      "Trump's caveat about naval blockade remaining until deal complete introduces implementation risk to watch."
    ]
  },
